  <bioghist id="aspace_26a8132f585aa36a823c55ae30876b57">
    <head>Biographical note</head>
<p>The Kasper family lived at the Manhattan Beach Veterans Housing Project in South Brooklyn in the late 1940s. Irving Kasper had been discharged from the U.S. army in 1945. Carol Kasper (now Hannan), the donor, attended dance classes in Brighton Beach around 1948. She and her brother Marvin attended school at the Floyd Bennett Field Naval Center. They got to school, along with other neighborhood children, via a pony cart owned by a neighbor. She also recalled that her father's aunt, Jennie "Jean" Kasper, worked at the Brooklyn Navy Yard for 30 years, including as assistant to Rear Admiral Joseph Coghlan during WWII.</p>  </bioghist>
